                <head>From the South</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Reports the entrance of an unidentified ship into Charleston Harbor as well
                    as the assembling of troops near Fort Pickens. The article also predicts an
                    impending attack on Fort Sumter if it is not evacuated.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Conspiracy to Drag Virginia out of the Union</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Harman</ln>
                        <fn>John</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Reports an attempt to bring together Virginia secessionists and Douglas
                    Democrats to achieve secession. The Spectator believes that this plot will fail,
                    especially since Douglas supporters do not blindly follow John Harman, who was
                    the Douglas Elector for the Augusta district and who is part of the plot.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
